<h3>📦 Installation</h3>
<p>Requires <a href="https://php.net/releases/" target="_blank">PHP 8.4+</a> and an <a href="https://www.arangodb.com/" target="_blank">ArangoDB 3.11+</a> server. Install via <a href="https://getcomposer.org/" target="_blank">Composer</a>:</p>
<pre class="language-bash prettyprint">composer require oihana/php-arango</pre>

<h3>✨ What you can do</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Talk to ArangoDB</strong> through a modern, ready-to-use HTTP client built on Guzzle — Basic + JWT/Bearer authentication, automatic 401 refresh, cluster failover, retry on transient errors.</li>
    <li><strong>Run AQL queries</strong> with safe placeholder binding (<code>aql()</code> helper), an <code>AqlBuilder</code> for fluent assembly, and a lazy <code>Cursor</code> supporting <code>map / forEach / reduce / flatMap</code>.</li>
    <li><strong>Manage collections, documents, edges and indexes</strong> — full CRUD, batch operations, bulk JSON-Lines import, 7 typed index types.</li>
    <li><strong>Use transactions, graphs, analyzers and views</strong> — streaming transactions with <code>withTransaction()</code> auto-commit/abort, gharial-based graphs, ArangoSearch analyzers and views.</li>
    <li><strong>Compose document models</strong> via fine-grained traits (CRUD, AQL helpers, signals before/after CRUD).</li>
    <li><strong>Plug controllers</strong> into any <a href="https://www.slimframework.com/" target="_blank">Slim</a>-compatible PSR-15 stack with <code>DocumentsController</code> + capability gating.</li>
    <li><strong>Drive list queries from the URL</strong> — a declarative <code>?search=</code>, <code>?filter=</code> and <code>?facets=</code> DSL that compiles to safe, bound AQL.</li>
</ul>

<h3>✅ Running tests</h3>
<p>Run all tests:</p>
<pre class="language-bash prettyprint">composer test</pre>
<p>Measure code coverage (requires Xdebug or PCOV):</p>
<pre class="language-bash prettyprint">composer coverage       # text + Clover + HTML report under build/coverage/
composer coverage:md    # readable Markdown summary at build/coverage/COVERAGE.md</pre>

